met<-met[temp> -17][elev==9999.0, elev :=NA]
met[, week := week(as.Date(paste(year, month, day, sep ="-")))]
met <- met[week == min(week, na.rm = TRUE)]
library(data.table)

met_avg <- met[
  ,
  .(
    temp      = mean(temp,      na.rm = TRUE),
    rh        = mean(rh,        na.rm = TRUE),
    wind.sp   = mean(wind.sp,   na.rm = TRUE),
    vis.dist  = mean(vis.dist,  na.rm = TRUE),
    dew.point = mean(dew.point, na.rm = TRUE),
    lat       = mean(lat,       na.rm = TRUE),
    lon       = mean(lon,       na.rm = TRUE),
    elev      = mean(elev,      na.rm = TRUE)
  ),
  by = USAFID
]
met_avg$region <- ifelse(met_avg$lon > -98 & met_avg$lat >39.71, "north east",
                         ifelse(met_avg$lon > -98 &
                                  met_avg$lat <39.71, "south east",
                                ifelse(met_avg$lon < -98 &met_avg$lat >39.71, 
                                       "north west", "south west")))
met_avg$elev_cat <- ifelse(met_avg$elev> 252, "high", "low")
table(met_avg$region)

Question 7

library(dplyr)
library(leaflet)

met_avg2 <- met_avg[!is.na(rh)]
top10 <- met_avg2[rank(-rh)]
rh_pal = colorNumeric(c('blue', 'purple', 'red'), domain=met_avg2$rh)



leaflet(met_avg2) %>%
  addProviderTiles("OpenStreetMap") %>%
  addCircles(
    lat = ~lat, lng = ~lon,
    color = ~rh_pal(rh), fillColor = ~rh_pal(rh),
    opacity = 1, fillOpacity = 0.8, radius = 500,
    label = ~paste0(round(rh, 2), "% RH")
  ) %>%
  addMarkers(
    data = top10,
    lat = ~lat, lng = ~lon,
    label = ~paste0(round(rh, 2), "%")
  ) %>%
  addLegend("bottomleft", pal = rh_pal, values = ~rh,
            title = "Relative Humidity (%)", opacity = 1)

Description From the interactive map, we can see that the humidity is lower in place like Los Angles and Las Vegas. This is the case probably do to its dessert landscape condition.

Question 8

library(ggplot2)
library(gganimate)
library(gifski)
library(dplyr)

# data: your averaged table `met_avg`
df <- met_avg %>%
  filter(is.finite(dew.point), is.finite(wind.sp), !is.na(region)) %>%
  mutate(region = droplevels(factor(region)))

p_reg <- ggplot(df, aes(dew.point, wind.sp, colour = region)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7, size = 1.6, show.legend = TRUE) +
  labs(title = "Region: {closest_state}",
       x = "Dew point (Â°C)", y = "Wind speed (m/s)") +
  transition_states(region, transition_length = 0.6, state_length = 1) +
  ease_aes("sine-in-out")

dir.create("figs", showWarnings = FALSE)
a <- animate(p_reg, renderer = gifski_renderer(),
             nframes = 40, fps = 12, width = 640, height = 360, progress = FALSE)
anim_save("figs/dew-wind_by-region.gif", animation = a)
